| [[Radio wave]]s (1887) || Radio had become used in innumerable ways beyond its better-known areas of [[telephony]], and [[broadcasting|broadcast]] [[television]] (1927) and [[radio station|radio]] (1906) [[entertainment]]. Other uses included&nbsp;– [[emergency services]], [[radar]] ([[navigation]] and [[weather prediction]]), [[medicine]], [[radio astronomy|astronomy]], [[wireless communications]], [[geophysics]], and [[wireless networking|networking]]. Radio waves also led researchers to adjacent frequencies such as [[microwave]]s, used worldwide for heating and cooking food.
